
Introduction To Mainframe:
================================
Mainframe:
------------
- Handling large amount of transfers
- processing
- bank transfers
- large amount of data
- security of realtime

Store of data
-------------
1.File system - QSAM, VSAM
2.Database system - IMS, DB2, IDMS, OTHERS

Processing of data
-------------------
1.Batch processing
2.Online processing

Batch:
------
1.huge of amount
2.scheduled
3.without user interaction
4.thr jcl
Ex:
----
1.Billing system,credit card,telecompost and bank statements
- I have a credit card- Billing date- 10th of each month
@ System -create a monthly bill -- all cust whose bill data is on 10th - dec 10th next month bill --> jan10th

Online system:
----------------
1.Short information of data
2.unscheduled
3. with user interaction
4. thr CICS/IMS
Ex: ATM/SWIPE CARD POS---> Next transactions are unscheduled 
                      ----> User needed --> yes

Batch Application:
------------------
->cobol --PGM lang--coding--condition business -calucaltion

1.Policy --->Dec10 2021 ----> Dec 092022 ==1 year---1,00,000
@ On case claim
           CASE1: On jan 10 2022- 2,00,000--- partial approved
           CASE2: 50,000 on dc 10 2022 approved-->Rejected
2.JCL--> Execution
3.File-> DB2- to store the data

Online Application:
----------------------
1.Cobol
2.CICS-->Execution
3.File-->DB2--> to store of the data

Batch--> Cobol,JCL,DB2
Online--> Cobol,CICS,DB2

COBOL:
--------
4 Divisions--section--paragraphs--statements(Instructions given to the system telling what to do)

Division:
-----------
4 dvisions
 1.Identification division
 2.Environment fivision
 3.Data division
 4.Procedure division

Identification Division:
---------------------------
 ID DIVISION.
 PROGRAM-ID. NAME OF THE PGM.
 AUTHOR. URNAME.
 DATA-WRITTEN. TODAY DATE
 DATE-COMPLETED. SAMES TODAY'S DATE.
 INSTALLATION. TEAM/APPLICATION NAME.
 SECURITY. WARNING MESSAGE IF ANY.
- Used to provide in PGM documentation details
- 6 para in this division
